<p>I&rsquo;ve never used the GitHub <code>gh</code> CLI at all really but I learned recently that you
can use it to set secrets to use them in GitHub Actions. SO much easier than
setting them from the web interface.</p>
<pre><code>gh secret set FLY_API_TOKEN
</code></pre>
<p>Also <code>gh auth token</code> is a great way to get a token to authenticate to the GitHub API, like this:</p>
<pre><code>export GITHUB_TOKEN=$(gh auth token)
curl -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer $GITHUB_TOKEN&quot; \
        https://api.github.com/repos/gohugoio/hugo/releases/tags/v0.136.0 | jq -r '.body'
</code></pre>
